Non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (s)
icroglial cells, closely related to the macrophage series of cells in the periphery, increase in size and number in the brain with . rom this observation and the presence of complement in amyloid plaques, the concept of  as an inflammatory disease has emerged. ore than 20 epidemiological studies, some with a follow-up design and a good estimation of s use via prescription data from pharmacies have suggested that the prolonged intake of s may be associated with a reduced incidence of 
[44]. n a anadian 10-year population-based cohort study, with the incidence of  (mild cognitive impairment or cognitive impairment, not dementia), , and all-cause dementia, it was shown that there is an association between  use and a lower incidence of 
