Estrogens
strogens are neuroprotective against oxidative stress, excitatory neurotoxicity, and ischemia in the brain. tudis shown that estradiol administration significantly ameliorates the neurodegeneration characteristic of  in experimental rat model. his may be attributed to its powerful antioxidant, antiapoptotic, neurotrophic as well as its antiamyloidogenic activities. erlo et al. reported that estrogen can activate matrix metalloproteinases-2 and β�’9 to increase beta amyloid degradation
[46]. eceptors within the forebrain are found on the same neurons as cholinergic receptors specifically affected by the pathologic changes in . t is speculated that the withdrawal of estrogen in postmenopausal women results in a predisposition to . he use of estrogen during hormone-replacement therapy () has also been posited as a neuroprotective treatment for . everal small short-term randomized clinical trials and some epidemiologic studies
